<blockquote>
  <p>&#8220;Why do doctors make more money than grape-pickers?&#8221;</p>
</blockquote>

<p>1) Because doctors have a very effective union in the US:
http://www.mises.org/fullstory.aspx?control=1547</p>

<p>2) Because doctors are in short supply. Partly because of their union and partly because it takes a long time, and a lot of money, to train to be a doctor. Grape picking doesn&#8217;t. Thus there&#8217;s a far greater supply of grape pickers.</p>

<p>AGL</p>

