</div><div id="c4760">

<p>You know, when I was taking an IHUM-style class as an undergrad, I often had incisive contributions to make, and the teacher often shut me down.  But my incisive contributions were usually the opposite of yours, politically.</p>

<p>So I suspect that the teacher trying to get you to shut up isn&#8217;t because of your politics but because you, like me, talked too much or were too socially deaf &#8212; e.g. failing to follow the social protocols of giving other people affirmation etc.</p>

<p>Regards,</p>

<p>Zooko</p>

